flowchart TB
    subgraph Indemnity [Traditional Indemnity Insurance]
        direction TB
        I1[Loss occurs]
        I2[Insured files claim<br/>with proof of loss]
        I3[Adjuster investigates<br/>Site inspection<br/>Document review]
        I4[Coverage analysis<br/>Is it within policy?<br/>Exclusions?<br/>Sublimits?]
        I5[Loss amount calculated<br/>Depreciation, actual cash value,<br/>replacement cost]
        I6[Negotiation &<br/>settlement]
        I7[Payment<br/>Days to months or years]

        I1 --> I2 --> I3 --> I4 --> I5 --> I6 --> I7
    end

    subgraph Parametric [Parametric Insurance]
        direction TB
        P1[Trigger event<br/>Cat 3 hurricane passes<br/>within 30 miles]
        P2[Objective measurement<br/>From authoritative source:<br/>NOAA, USGS, weather station]
        P3[Trigger check<br/>Did measurement meet<br/>predefined threshold?]
        P4[Automatic payout<br/>Predefined amount<br/>No loss investigation]
        P5[Payment<br/>Hours to days]

        P1 --> P2 --> P3 --> P4 --> P5
    end

    subgraph Tradeoffs [Key Tradeoffs]
        Basis[Basis Risk<br/>Parametric may pay<br/>without loss,<br/>or loss without payout]
        Speed[Speed<br/>Parametric: Days<br/>Indemnity: Months]
        Fit[Fit to loss<br/>Indemnity matches actual<br/>Parametric approximates]
        LAE[Loss Adjustment Expense<br/>Parametric: Near zero<br/>Indemnity: 8-15% of premium]
    end

    Indemnity -.Slower, exact.-> Fit
    Parametric -.Faster, approximate.-> Basis

    style Indemnity fill:#fff3e0,stroke:#e65100,stroke-width:2px
    style Parametric fill:#c8e6c9,stroke:#1b5e20,stroke-width:2px
    style Tradeoffs fill:#e1f5fe,stroke:#01579b,stroke-width:2px
